com.google.closure.plugin.plan

Class PlanGraphNode<V extends PlanGraphNode.StateVector>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.closure.plugin.plan.PlanGraphNode<V>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompilePlanGraphNode, JoinNodes.JoinPlanGraphNode, OptionPlanGraphNode, SourceSpecedPlanGraphNode, TeePlanGraphNode

    public abstract class PlanGraphNode<V extends PlanGraphNode.StateVector>
extends Object
    A plan graph node is a node in the builder graph.

    The lifecycle of a plan graph node is

    1. Check inputs to see whether anything has changed.
    2. Process input files.
    3. Update the follower list.
    4. Mark outputs that have changed.

    After a compile, the graph can be serialized. Serializing a plan graph involves serializing each node's state-vector and the edges.

    When its time to do an incremental recompilation, the plan graph can be reconstituted via PlanGraphNode.StateVector.reconstitute(com.google.closure.plugin.plan.PlanContext, com.google.closure.plugin.plan.JoinNodes).
